<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="677" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Merry</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-10"><hi rend="italic">July 10,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Merry reports that all efforts for peace are useless. Salvadorian
                            general commanding forced fight on Guatemala territory; civil
                            authorities favored peace. He suggests war vessel on the coast,
                            Declaration of war is not yet made.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>